    "This decomposition enables isolating treatment-driven variations as outcomes evolve during the experiment.",
    "However, in certain settings, this invariance property is unrealistic.",
    "Exposure mechanisms may themselves shift with treatment.",
    "For example, in systems with threshold dynamics where peer influence activates only after a critical mass of the treatment adoption, the required decomposition does not hold.",
    "Relying on treatment-driven variations over time also constrains the applicability of evolutionbased frameworks."
